RACE.RACE_TEXT: Fresno Dash S. FRESNO RACE 1 350 Y Dirt CR: 86. Stakes Purse 20000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD (QUARTER HORSES). No nomination fee. $100 to enter. $20,000 Guaranteed of which 55% to the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 7% to fourth, 2% to fifth and sixth, and 1% to seventh and eighth. (In the event there are fewer than eight runners the purse monies will be prorated.) . Weight: three-years-old, 123 lbs.; older 126 lbs. Closed Sunday, October 8, 2023 with 20 nominations. Preference by monies earned in 2022-2023. No sex allowance.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THREE TIMES A LADY broke on top,held narrow lead stretch,kept to task late,held. DOLLYS TALENT vied,drifted in 1/8,battled deep stretch,outfinished,held 2nd. APPROVAL GIVEN close up,outkicked deep stretch,held 3rd. FORTUNATE CORONA broke in,chased from back,mild late rally. BLITZ CHICK chased mid-pack,weakened. TWO TIMIN TAYLOR broke in/shuffled start,no threat. WALK TO THE TOP chased,took up/shuffled back 1/8,no late rally. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE INCIDENT IN MID-STRETCH INVOLVING DOLLYS TALENT DRIFTING IN. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION THE STEWARDS RULED THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 95. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And All owances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOO WOP DON bobbled leaving the start and was off a step slowly, tracked the decent pace from the inside, was roused in upper stretch and vied for the lead heading to the furlong marker, took command, met the late bid of FAR WEST held a narrow advantage in the final sixteenth, dug in late and lasted for the win at the finish. FAR WEST tracked the decent pace outside of rivals, advanced three wide into the turn and pressed the pace to the quarter marker, lost a bit of ground into the stretch and chased to the furlong grounds, re-rallied into deep stretch, confronted DOO WOP DON approaching the sixteenth-marker, battled with that foe into deep stretch, could not get by the determined winner in the final strides and held safely for second. SATANTA was allowed to settle away from the start, tracked between rivals to the half-mile marker, was steered outside of runners and improved position four wide heading to the quarter pole, swung widest into the lane and mounted a four wide rally into the stretch, closed in the final furlong, could not reel in the top two in the late stages and held clearly for third. MITICO sent at the start, dictated terms in the early running and carved a decent pace into the turn, set the pace off of the rail and was pressed to the quarter marker by FAR WEST, battled for the lead into the stretch with DOO WOP DON, could not keep pace into the final sixteenth and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Mitico
ENTRY.OWNER: Dudzik Michael Garthwaite Eric and Salvatore Raymond L
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,set pressured pace turn,battled upper stretch,weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Satanta

ENTRY.NAME: Far West

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $3,50 0 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POUR ON THE COLE never far back, settled outside of runners to begin, tracked the modest pace while well placed through the backstretch run, loomed four wide along the far turn and took command into the stretch, drew to a clear lead at the furlong pole, drew off under hand urging in the final stages and was much the best in the end. BABY FRANKIE was prominent in the early running and contested the pace along the first turn inside of BENNY THE JET, took command along the backstretch run and set a modest pace while pressured to the half-mile marker, held a slim lead into the far turn, was unable to match strides with POUR ON THE COLE into the stretch, drifted out in the lane and chased the winner to the furlong grounds, was no match for the winner in the final furlong and was best of the rest. BEL RAGAZZO settled just off of the early pace, stalked from the two path along the first turn and tracked the modest pace through the backstretch run, advanced three wide into the far turn and vied for the lead nearing the quarter marker, could not keep pace with POUR ON THE COLE into the stretch and chased to the furlong marker, faded in the final stages, was outfinished for second and was well clear for third. BENNY THE JET was forwardly placed into the first turn, assumed command and set a pressured pace while off of the rail into the backstretch run, disputed the pace with BABY FRANKIE along the backstretch run, raced two wide between rivals into the far turn and came in a bit tight nearing the quarter marker, dropped back approaching the top of the stretch and tired in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR. BUGS was forwardly placed away from the start, tracked the decent early pace outside of runners, improved position four then three wide along the turn, vied for the lead into upper stretch, battled with LET GEORGE DO IT to the furlong marker, took command and shook clear into deep stretch, felt late pressure from the runner-up and held safely in a drive at the finish to prevail. DARK MYSTERY settled outside of an inner rival to begin, improved position three wide along the turn and was roused four wide into the stretch, came within aim approaching the furlong marker while widest, closed willingly in deep stretch, put pressure on the winner in the final strides but could not reel that one in and bested the rest. BRONZE ONE rushed up in the early stages and raced close to the decent early pace, lost position two wide along the turn, re-rallied into the stretch and gained ground approaching the furlong pole, could not muster a final response in deep stretch, was outkicked and just held for third at the finish. APLOMBADO bobbled at the start and was off a bit slowly, chased the early pace from the inside and saved ground to the top of the stretch, improved position heading to the furlong grounds, needed more in the late stages, mounted a mild rally in the final sixteenth and just missed for third. LET GEORGE DO IT showed good early speed away from the gate, dictated terms in the opening furlong and set a decent pace into the turn, showed the way to the quarter marker off of the rail, came under pressure into the stretch and battled to the furlong marker, lacked a response in deep stretch and weakened. EL CAPRICHO chased the decent early pace from a two wide path, lost a bit of ground heading to the quarter marker, was coaxed along three wide into the stretch, could not keep pace into the late stages and gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 78. Maiden Claiming Purse 12500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRANNIGAN pressed the decent early pace outside of GO GABRIELLA, took command into the turn and showed the way to the quarter marker while off of the rail, drew off into the stretch, was kept to steady urging into the final sixteenth, was all out to hold off O'BANION in deep stretch and lasted for the win at the finish. O'BANION (IRE) was prominent away from the start, took back in the early running and tracked from the second flight heading to the half-mile marker, raced two wide into the turn, angled four wide approaching the top of the lane and was asked for run into the stretch, chased BRANNIGAN to the furlong grounds, closed with a rush into deep stretch, came within aim in the final strides and just missed for the win, while well clear for second. BOBBED N LURED broke alertly and was prominent away from the start, stalked the decent early pace while outside of runners, gained ground three wide into the turn, could not keep pace with BRANNIGAN into the stretch, was unable to make headway on the winner in the drive and was outkicked, while clear in the end for third. THECHIEFHASTRICKS chased outside of an inner rival leaving the start, came three wide into the turn, improved position into the stretch but was unable to threaten in the final furlong. GO GABRIELLA was hard sent leaving the break, set a decent early pace from the inside and was pressed into the turn, lost the lead into the bend and chased from the rail into upper stretch, lacked a response in the drive and tired. SMILING PREACHER stumbled at the start and was off slowly, chased the decent early pace while inside of rival, was coaxed along in the three path into the turn, lost contact approaching the top of the lane and did not factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Go Gabriella
ENTRY.OWNER: Orsi Bernardo and Schmitt George F
ENTRY.COMMENT: hard sent,set pace inside,lost lead 3/8,chased inside

ENTRY.NAME: Brannigan
ENTRY.OWNER: Perez Sergio S and Abrahamson Joe
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed early pace,led turn,clear 1/8,all out late,lasted

ENTRY.NAME: Thechiefhastricks
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased outside,3wd turn,improved position stretch,no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Bobbed N Lured
ENTRY.OWNER: Daehling Farms LLC and Stortz Marcia

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 6 1M Dirt CR: 98. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Clai ming, And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRONZE WARRIOR was asked for speed away from the start, vied outside of a pair of rivals into the first turn and assumed command three then two wide into the backstretch run, set solid fractions along the backstretch run and extended the lead heading to the half-mile marker, came under pressure from LIL MIRACLE MAN approaching the quarter marker, met that bid into upper stretch and battled to the furlong grounds, shook free into deep stretch, dug in under firm urging in the late stages and held safely in the end for a determined win. LORD WIMBORNE (IRE) broke out at the start, was shuffled back and was off a bit slowly away from the gate, settled outside of an inner rival in the early running, tracked the solid fractions along the backstretch run, made a steady gain three wide into the far turn and came three wide into the stretch, closed well in the late stages, could not reel in the winner in deep stretch and was up in the final strides to secure second. LOOKOUT POINT was unhurried away from the start, settled in the two path into the backstretch run and tracked the pace to the half-mile marker, came two wide into the far turn, was roused four wide into the stretch and chased to the furlong pole, rallied in deep stretch and just missed for second, while just getting up for third in a blanket finish for the minor awards. LIL MIRACLE MAN vied for the early lead away from the start, took back into the first turn and stalked the pace from a two wide path into the backstretch run, raced close to the solid pace three deep approaching the half-mile marker, mounted a two wide bid approaching the quarter pole and battled for the lead into the stretch, pressured BRONZE WARRIOR to the furlong marker, lost ground to that rival into deep stretch, lacked a response in the final sixteenth and was outfinished for the minor awards. IL CAPITANO broke out a bit at the start and was off a step slowly, recovered to be forwardly placed into the first turn, checked off of heels when BRONZE WARRIOR crossed over into the backstretch run, stalked the pacesetter through solid fractions to the half-mile marker, saved ground into the far turn, lost position approaching the quarter marker, trailed into the stretch and weakened in the late stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Lord Wimborne (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out start,settled outside,closed well 3wd stretch,up for 2d

ENTRY.NAME: Bronze Warrior
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent,set solid pace,met bid 1/4,shook free late,dug in,determined

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 27000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $25,0 00 (Non-starters For Claiming Price $16,000 Or Less In The Last Three Starts Preferred)(Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won An Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs. Unless Entered For A ClaimingP rice).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAMARA MINE disputed the solid early pace with TIP TOP GAL, took command along the turn and set the pace from the two path heading to the quarter marker, was pressed into the stretch by CITY GLITTER and fought with that rival into upper stretch, repelled that bid and was confronted again by TIP TOP GAL approaching the furlong pole, battled with that foe into deep stretch, held a narrow lead in the final yards and determinedly lasted for the win at the finish. CITY GLITTER raced close to the decent early pace while outside of rivals, advanced on the turn and pressed the pace three wide to the quarter marker, was turned away into upper stretch and chased to the furlong pole, re-rallied into the final sixteenth, finished well in deep stretch and missed for the win, while getting up in time to secure the place. TIP TOP GAL was away in good order and contested the decent early pace with TAMARA MINE, lost ground to that rival into the turn and chased from the inside into upper stretch, re-bid approaching the furlong marker and vied for the lead into mid-stretch, could not get by the determined winner into deep stretch, was outfinished for second in the final strides and was well clear of the rest for third. YOUNG LIFE LAURA broke in at the start, sharply bumped NAN ELIZABETH and caused that runner to unseat her rider, spotted the field in the early stages, chased two wide along the turn and did not threaten. NOMI LACKEE chased the decent early pace from the inside, was outrun along the turn and gave way in the stretch. NAN ELIZABETH was bumped sharply at the start by YOUNG LIFE LAURA, unseated the rider in the first few jumps away from the gate, was caught following the race and walked off under her own power. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE START OF THE RACE. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT YOUNG LIFE LAURA INTERFERED WITH NAN ELIZABETH LEAVING THE START AND WOULD BE DISQUALIFIED FROM FOURTH AND PLACED LAST.

ENTRY.OWNER: Gabriel Luciano Medina and Zhu Xuewen

ENTRY.OWNER: Perez Sergio S Abrahamson Joe and Filos Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in sharply start,off slowly,chased 2wd turn,no threat

ENTRY.COMMENT: disputed early pace,speed 2p,repelled foes stretch,determined win

ENTRY.NAME: City Glitter
ENTRY.OWNER: Martin, Jerry R. and Margaret M.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FRESNO RACE 8 5F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since August 15 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500 (Maiden, Claiming, And Starter Races For $1,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAKER JET raced with the tracking group early on then was outrun on the turn as TWO TWELVE stretched the field out on the lead, started a bid passing the three furlong marker, swung out to the four path for the stretch run, made a good late rally along with SEVEN SISTERS, made up a half-dozen lengths in the final furlong, got a head in front with yards to go and prevailed in a thrilling finish. SEVEN SISTERS broke best and had the lead for a few strides, then angled over to save ground while letting TWO TWELVE take command into the turn, set down after that rival for the stretch run, was gradually cutting into the margin down the lane, passed that foe in the shadow of the wire but could not hold off LAKER JET in the final jumps. TWO TWELVE vied for the early lead from the break, emerged from the pack with the lead passing the nine-sixteenths pole then opened up on the field through the turn, came under pressure at the top of the stretch, was weakening passing the eighth pole and could not hold off a pair of closers to the outside but soldiered on to hold third. TAKES A VILLAGE got a perfect inside trip, raced up close to the pace in the early stages under some encouragement, tracked behind TWO TWELVE through the turn, got even with SEVEN SISTERS nearing the quarter pole, came into the stretch with every chance and ran on well but came up short of a minor award. COASTAL STARLITE broke well then was unable to keep up with the dueling leaders, raced to the inside of the tracking group then lost some ground on the turn but kept to task and finished up with some interest and not too far behind the winner. ALESHA was last away, angled over the rail for the run through the turn, was put into a drive from the seven-sixteenths pole, had too much ground to make up but did improve somewhat in the final furlong. MISCHIEF MAMA fell behind after the break despite the best efforts of the rider to encourage some speed, found a good rhythm heading into the the turn racing three wide but could not muster a rally. HOW ABOUT A FRESCA raced between horses as part of the tracking group through the initial furlong then began to fall behind as the field entered the turn and never recovered.

ENTRY.NAME: Takes a Village
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside trip, bid turn, good finish but needed more
